event.description:

A couple moves to Los Angeles to make their dreams of becoming successful in the music business a reality.
Silent Night -- James Foley
Two mental hospital attendants who disagree with each other’s methods care for a group of eccentric patients on Christmas Eve.
Proof -- Kevin Reynolds
A timid young man makes the skydiving jump of his life.

Friends and Neighbors Day
event.description:
We offer more than 50 different projects for you to work with local non-profits in the surrounding neighborhood of USC!
Projects include the following Beach clean-up Beautification Projects Community Gardening Projects Friendly Visiting Hunger and Homelessness Painting Projects SCitizen And MORE!
All registered volunteers will start the day with a free breakfast and then venture off with their teams to their designated project sites. Teams will return in the early afternoon for a free picnic in Alumni Park!
You will also get a free Friends and Neighbors Day shirt!
Visit our website to register for the event! www.usc.edu/volunteer

event.name: Natalie Portman Speaks on Behalf of FINCA's Village Banking Campaign
event.description:
USG Program Board Speakers Committee and USC Global Business Leaders (Globus) welcome you to a discussion with actress Natalie Portman.
Ms. Portman is a spokesperson for FINCA International's Village Banking Campaign, which aims to bring financial services to one million of the world’s lowest-income families through 100,000 Village Banks by 2010. Ms. Portman will discuss her involvement and experience promoting microlending, share stories and video of her recent travels to Mexico and Uganda, and will also answer audience questions.
“Join Natalie Portman on The Village Banking Campaign’s groups on Facebook and MySpace!”
VBC Facebook URL: http://www.facebook.com/group.php?gid=5247546234
VBC MySpace URL: www.myspace.com/villagebanking
**The event is free and only open to both undergraduate and graduate students of the University of Southern California. USC ID'S WILL BE CHECKED UPON ENTRY**
~~No cameras allowed inside~~

event.name: Reel World Chile
event.description:
Come enjoy free Chilean food while learning more about Chile.
---Donate a dollar so a child can learn--- In Chile: although public school is compulsory up to the eighth grade, many children are unable to attend because their families cannot afford required supplies and uniforms. School dropouts and poor school performance also must be combated. Please give your Resident Advisor a dollar towards this cause, and we will put up a miniature Chilean flag with your name on it in the lobby of Parkside Suites in recognition of your support. You will also be able to make donations at Reel World Chile, at 6pm on 10/21/07 between Parkside Apartments and the Performance Café.
